{
  "texts": [
    "• Logistic Regression (LR): Logistic regression is frequently used to predict \"successful\" or \"unsuccessful\", \"failed\" or \"survived\" for business prediction tasks.",
    "It is one of the mostly used algorithms due to its simplify and easy to interpret for business success prediction.",
    "A previous study (Żbikowski and Antosiuk 2021) has compared LR with SVM and XGBoost to predict successful and unsuccessful firms with target variable as 0 ('operating' or 'funding series b') and 1 ('acquired' and 'IPO').",
    "By using an exhaustive grid search as hyper-parameter tuning, LR achieved an accuracy of 86%, however, the recall score of 0.21 was observed which improved to 0.34 when XGBoost classifier was used.",
    "• Decision Tree (DT): Decision tree models are used for classification as well as regression tasks."
  ]
}